The paper deals with privacy issues induced by hashtags, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a system called Tagvisor that suggests alternative hashtags to protect location privacy, which involves semantic analysis (cs.SI) and data obfuscation (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the implications of location privacy on popular culture and campaigns, which falls under the category of cyberculture (cs.CY). Finally, the paper proposes a practical solution for real-world settings, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
